Assist in the controlled release of bodies; and preparation of deceased for
viewing and identification purposes, and provide assistance to the pathologist
with photography of deceased and collection, labelling and processing of
specimens.

** Key competencies (role specific criteria) **

You will be assessed on your ability to demonstrate, or rapidly acquire the
skills to demonstrate the following:

  * Pathology laboratory experience with ability to follow both written and oral instruction and identify and solve problems methodically. 
  * Reliability, integrity, and professional attitude necessary for a medico-legal and potentially hazardous workplace. 
  * A high level computer and information technology skills with the ability to learn and use Auslab (case management system), QIS2 (quality system) and Microsoft software or equivalent computer applications within a mortuary environment. 
  * Understanding of relevant legislation and guidelines and their application to a department undertaking medico-legal autopsies. 
  * Sound judgement, ability to think critically, effective communication and interpersonal skills, with the proven ability to work in a team and contribute positively to team outcomes. 
  * Ability to proactively maintain a safe, secure and clean working environment and an understanding of and willingness to contribute to the relevant systems, processes and procedures. 

##  Qualifications, registrations and other requirements

  * It may be a condition of employment for this role for the employee to be, and remain, vaccinated against one or more of the following vaccine preventable diseases during their employment ( [ Health Employment ](https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/150120/hed-0116.pdf) [ ](https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/150120/hed-0116.pdf) [ Directive No. 01/16 ](https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/150120/hed-0116.pdf) [ ) ](https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/150120/hed-0116.pdf) : measles, mumps, rubella (MMR),varicella (chicken pox),pertussis (whooping cough),hepatitis B, tuberculosis 
  * Additional vaccinations including Japanese Encephalitis and Rabies may also be required for this position. 
  * Please detail any visa conditions you may have if you are not a permanent resident of Australia. 
  * We understand that some people may require adjustments to the workplace or the way the work is performed. All applicants are encouraged to advise the panel of any support or reasonable adjustments (i.e., building access, wheelchair access, interpreting services etc.) that may be required. 

##  Additional Information

Please provide the following information to the panel to assess your
suitability:

  * Your ** resume ** , including the names and contact details of two referees who have a thorough knowledge of your capabilities, work performance and conduct within the previous two years, and it is preferable to include your current, immediate, or past supervisor. 
  * A ** statement of suitability of no more than two pages ** addressing your ability to meet the requirements of the role. 

